    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Moses was not to muster the tribe of Levi along with the children of Israel, i.e., with the other tribes, or take their number, but to appoint the Levites for the service of the dwelling of the testimony (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 38:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), i.e., of the tabernacle, that they might encamp around it, might take it down when the camp was broken up, and set it up when Israel encamped again, and that no stranger (zar, non-Levite, as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 22:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") might come near it and be put to death (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 3:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The rest of the tribes were to encamp every man in his place of encampment, and by his banner (see at ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 2:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), in their hosts (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), that wrath might not come upon the congregation, viz., through the approach of a stranger. קצף, the wrath of Jehovah, breaking in judgment upon the unholy who approached His sanctuary in opposition to His command (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
